DataElement.preferredDefinition: An approach to modeling a protein structure based on an initial sequence alignment to a protein with a known 3D structure.  After evaluating and resolving structural irregularities in the initial model, it may be further refined using energy minimization and other procedures.:The amino acids and their 3-D arrangement in constituting a protein.
